narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Graphic design and thinking how to creatively express more advanced conceptual ideas
how to fine tune a graphic design project over several weeks including a poster series and flexibility visual identity
AGD allows the student to perform a deep-dive into two main projects, learning about the process of design as well as focusing on producing a polished outcome.
I learned how to create a successful dynamic identity, in addition to creating a series of sequential posters.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Its a great course. Henk definitely cares about everyones learning and hes a great prof

I enjoyed the pacing of the course. We focused on two main projects. On the other hand, I think it couldve been helpful to have some technical exercises, or other demonstrations around the process of designing and structuring a project.
The course allows for deep focus on two specific projects. There was one day of collaborative work that I learned a lot from  I would recommend introducing more of those collaborative days!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: 100%. This is one of the best design courses offered to undergraduates. Only two projects ensures sufficient time is allowed to fully flesh out design ideas. And Henk gives great feedback
Yes, its a flexible class that allows you to develop two graphic design projects with topics informed by your interests.

Absolutely! Henk is an amazing professor with strong ability to lead and direct what is largely a self-motivated studio course. This is an amazing course to take if youre confident in your design abilities but would benefit from consistent crits.
Yes! Henk is awesome, and will provide good feedback and guidance for your projects.
